# Modeling Strategy

Models evaluated

- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest
- Gradient Boosting

Evaluation strategy

- Stratified Train/Validation/Test Split
- Class imbalance awareness
- Threshold optimization
- Out-of-sample evaluation
- PR-AUC optimization
- Cost-sensitive evaluation
- Permutation Feature Importance

---

# Key Results

After redesigning the synthetic data generation process to include realistic infrastructure failure signals, predictive performance improved substantially.

| Metric | Result |
|---------|---------|
| Test AUC | ~0.82 |
| PR-AUC | ~0.67 |
| F1 Score | ~0.60 |
| Accuracy | ~85% |

The final model demonstrated meaningful predictive capability for operational access failures.

---

# Most Important Predictors

Permutation Feature Importance identified the following operational drivers.

| Rank | Feature |
|------|-----------|
| 1 | API Latency |
| 2 | Middleware Timeout |
| 3 | Session Timeout |
| 4 | OTP Failure |
| 5 | External Dependency Failure |
| 6 | Token Mismatch |
| 7 | Application Crash |
| 8 | Network Drop |

Operational timing variables such as retry count and peak hour showed comparatively lower predictive value after controlling for infrastructure failures.

---

# Threshold Optimization

Rather than maximizing overall accuracy, prediction thresholds were optimized to minimize missed operational failures.

The project evaluates

- Precision
- Recall
- F1 Score
- PR-AUC
- Operational Cost

This reflects real banking operations where **missing a critical failure is significantly more expensive than generating a false alert**.

---

# Cost-Sensitive Modeling

Business costs were incorporated into threshold selection.

```
False Negative  >>  False Positive
```

Objective:

Reduce missed operational failures while maintaining acceptable false alarm rates.

---

# Segment Analysis

Operational performance was evaluated across

- Customer channels
- Branch clusters
- Infrastructure conditions

This enables operations teams to identify high-risk operational segments requiring targeted intervention.

---

# Early Warning System

The final stage of the project demonstrates how predictive analytics can support real-time banking operations.

Operational workflow

```
Incoming Transaction

        │

        ▼

Feature Extraction

        │

        ▼

Predictive Model

        │

        ▼

Risk Score

        │

        ▼

Threshold Check

        │

        ▼

Alert Generation

        │

        ▼

Operations Dashboard

        │

        ▼

Manual Investigation
```

The framework illustrates how predictive models can transition from experimentation into production-oriented monitoring systems.

